Map

for making map and zones

sonetilhorighet.txt is the list of all farms (about 4000) with zone, lat, long Lokaliteter.csv is the list of the current active farms (farm with fish), Norwaymap.zip has the files for generating production zones

Below are the links to examples of the interactive maps we are using: https://www.barentswatch.no/fiskehelse/settings https://portal.fiskeridir.no/portal/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=87d862c458774397a8466b148e3dd147

farms_all <- read_table2("sonetilhorighet.txt", locale = locale(decimal_mark = ",")) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.character, ~ gsub('"', '', .))

-- Column specification ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
cols(
  `"LokNr"` = col_character(),
  `"sone"` = col_character(),
  `"EastUTM_33N_WGS84"` = col_double(),
  `"NorthUTM_33N_WGS84"` = col_double(),
  `"Longitude_WGS84"` = col_double(),
  `"Latitude_WGS84"` = col_double()
)
names(farms_all) <- c("loc_nr", "zone", "east_utm", "north_utm", "lon", "lat")
farms_all
farms_active <- read_csv("Lokaliteter.csv") %>% 
  rename("loc_nr" = "loknr") %>% 
  mutate(loc_nr = as.character(loc_nr))

-- Column specification ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
cols(
  .default = col_character(),
  loknr = col_double(),
  kapasitet_lok = col_double(),
  breddegrader = col_double(),
  lengdegrader = col_double(),
  objectid = col_double(),
  shape = col_logical(),
  x = col_double(),
  y = col_double()
)

filter(farms_active, !loc_nr %in% farms_all$loc_nr)
